          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780142417119" href="/book/show/7261699-eon">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/21937982-hailey-hailey-in-bookland?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/21937982-hailey-hailey-in-bookland?shelf=owned">owned</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1020297316" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9715530152583213165">I wanted to love it, but I just couldn&apos;t. The lack of explanations just killed it for me. This book had no setting, though I&apos;m assuming it&apos;s China. But it&apos;s never mentioned, and to me that&apos;s a pretty fundamental aspect of a book. The plot was really quite cool and exciting once you got more into the book, but it took me forever to get there because it was pretty slow and I kept having to reread things to try and understand what was going on. Not sure if I&apos;ll end up picking up book 2.</span>
  <span id="freeText9715530152583213165" style="display:none">I wanted to love it, but I just couldn't. The lack of explanations just killed it for me. This book had no setting, though I'm assuming it's China. But it's never mentioned, and to me that's a pretty fundamental aspect of a book. The plot was really quite cool and exciting once you got more into the book, but it took me forever to get there because it was pretty slow and I kept having to reread things to try and understand what was going on. Not sure if I'll end up picking up book 2.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9715530152583213165" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

